.TH "efi_capsule_supported" 9 "efi_capsule_supported" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_capsule_supported \- does the firmware support the capsule?
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" efi_capsule_supported
.BI "(efi_guid_t guid "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "int *reset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "guid" 12
vendor guid of capsule
.IP "flags" 12
capsule flags
.IP "size" 12
size of capsule data
.IP "reset" 12
the reset type required for this capsule
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check whether a capsule with \fIflags\fP is supported by the firmware
and that \fIsize\fP doesn't exceed the maximum size for a capsule.

No attempt is made to check \fIreset\fP against the reset type required
by any pending capsules because of the races involved.
